Daily Max Changes in Pressure vs.Â Tide

The correlation between daily maximum atmospheric pressure changes and daily maximum tide level changes is analyzed. It is expected to show more significant trend as the amplitudes (daily_max - daily_min) are now used instead of the averaged difference (the daily averaged tide level difference between the day and the previous day). As seen, the daily max atmospheric pressure changes did not show a significant correlation to the tide level changes.

Daily wind vs.Â tide difference in 72 wedges

The correlation between daily wind speed and daily tide level difference are plotted by 72 wedges (5 degree per wedge, the ranges are stated on each title of the sub-plots). It is expected to show the influence of wind direction on the correlation between wind speed and tide difference. As seen, there is positive correlation between tide level and wind speed on the (-2.5, 227.5] (east) direction, while there is a negative correlation on the (227.5,357.5] (west) direction, which is consistent with the result in the 8 wedges plot. Some sub-plots on the north direction do not have trend lines due to the limited sample numbers.
